                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-368" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES HAYWARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I found the prisoner at the Waterman's Arms, at the back of Shoreditch church, dancing with a number of boys and girls—I was in plain clothes—I asked him if he knew me—he said, "Yes"—I told him what I took him for—he said he had lost the money; and after that he said he fell in with three young men, who asked him to go with them and drink, that he said he had no money but his router's, and they said, "Never mind, come"—he went with them, and spent 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and he was ashamed to go back—he gave some other account afterwards.</p>
